in the Donetsk region.

592
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:52,000
I can't just go to their cemetery,
because someone came to liberate that land.

593
00:36:54,729 --> 00:36:59,822
I have enough motivation, and
it won't cease for a very long time.

594
00:36:59,847 --> 00:37:02,483
There will be as much as it takes of it.

595
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:04,435
So, there is hatred?

596
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:12,897
Well, I had it at first, and now, it's not just work,

597
00:37:12,922 --> 00:37:17,000
you just know that it's an enemy, that he
came, that he wants to do something with you.

598
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:20,000
If you don't kill him,
he will kill you.

599
00:37:20,433 --> 00:37:25,571
And this enemy has been here for a long time, and
he just needs to be eliminated, and that's it.

600
00:37:25,898 --> 00:37:29,000
Hatred, it's probably more
about civil people, because,

601
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:35,000
well, they view it in another way.

602
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:37,492
When you've been working...

603
00:37:38,386 --> 00:37:41,928
The biggest motivation for me
at the moment,

604
00:37:43,324 --> 00:37:49,000
obviously, is to return to our borders
and all that,

605
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:55,000
but I want revenge for the brother-in-arms, which
they killed because there won't be anyone like them.

606
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:58,000
Do they come to you?

607
00:37:59,000 --> 00:37:59,750
They come.

608
00:37:59,775 --> 00:38:01,000
Yes.

609
00:38:01,025 --> 00:38:02,990
Even recently, yes.

610
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:12,139
Decent people come, we work with them, and then they fit in the
team, in the family, in the unit,

611
00:38:12,177 --> 00:38:19,274
because you have not only to fit
in the unit by head, but also by heart.

612
00:38:19,299 --> 00:38:23,542
It is necessary to become not a
person in Azov, but the Azovian himself,

613
00:38:23,858 --> 00:38:28,653
There is a category, this is my...

614
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:29,871
Invention?

615
00:38:29,896 --> 00:38:31,000
Subjective opinion,

616
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:38,000
there are people who do it for money,

617
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,000
some do it for something else,

618
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:43,273
and there are people who just come,

619
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:46,000
I really hope that we don't have such people,

620
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:51,000
but there are people who come
purely for commercial purposes.

621
00:38:52,185 --> 00:38:52,975
In Azov?

622
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:58,939
Well, I don't think it is true for Azov, but in other units, yes.

623
00:39:00,557 --> 00:39:01,326
I know this...

624
00:39:01,351 --> 00:39:02,975
Do you condemn such people?

625
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,000
Well, yes.

626
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:05,000
Really?

627
00:39:05,497 --> 00:39:08,947
I'm paid one hundred thousand hryvnias,
it doesn't matter if I die.'

628
00:39:09,646 --> 00:39:10,975
Their motivation...

629
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:12,000
But they do the work.

630
00:39:12,025 --> 00:39:14,471
Yes, they work, but their motivation is money.

631
00:39:15,643 --> 00:39:28,334
How money can be a motivation when your country is being destroyed, civil people are dying, and children, and women?

632
00:39:31,009 --> 00:39:35,839
What other motivation is there? Money?

633
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:40,000
What if to consider it compensation

634
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:45,975
for the fact that you are freezing, working, digging?

635
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:49,000
In general, it doesn't bother me.

636
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:57,353
I would agree to compensate my
parents for the fact that my mother does not see her son.

637
00:39:59,195 --> 00:40:02,599
Let me eat, take a bath, and wash my clothes.

638
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:04,480
I don't need anything else.

639
00:40:06,651 --> 00:40:07,829
Okay.

640
00:40:08,582 --> 00:40:15,975
When I am a civilian, when the war
ends, then I will think about money,

641
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:17,369
how to build your civilian life further.

642
00:40:17,394 --> 00:40:18,406
But where...

643
00:40:18,431 --> 00:40:21,049
I mean, I understand it, but not really.

644
00:40:21,087 --> 00:40:24,423
I will go away,
and I will still think about your words.

645
00:40:24,448 --> 00:40:27,415
Look, everyone has their own story.

646
00:40:27,440 --> 00:40:30,055
The money is important to someone.

647
00:40:32,189 --> 00:40:39,746
Maybe, someone is serving and
building a house at the time, or investing.

648
00:40:39,771 --> 00:40:41,480
I do not judge.

649
00:40:41,505 --> 00:40:47,715
I'm telling the truth, it is my subjective opinion.

650
00:40:47,740 --> 00:40:48,925
I think so.

651
00:40:48,976 --> 00:40:53,975
I do not impose my opinion on anyone,
it's just my point of view.

652
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:55,452
I am cool this way.

653
00:40:56,000 --> 00:41:02,000
Azov is such a unit, which
is shrouded in legends,

654
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:06,810
and the tragedy that happened in 2022.

655
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:10,840
There was a series of tragedies.

656
00:41:10,864 --> 00:41:19,387
Their exit, despite the order to save lives, is also a tragedy.

657
00:41:19,411 --> 00:41:24,414
Because later there were Olenivka and tortures.

658
00:41:24,771 --> 00:41:29,160
Do guys that have been through it tell you something?

659
00:41:29,827 --> 00:41:34,576
Do they talk sincerely? Are there moments of soldier truth?

660
00:41:34,600 --> 00:41:36,502
Of course, there are.

661
00:41:36,526 --> 00:41:39,715
We try not to ask about it.

662
00:41:39,739 --> 00:41:43,487
We understand how it is there and what is going on there.

663
00:41:44,407 --> 00:41:56,070
We try not to bother them with it so that they do not
return in their thoughts to what they went through there.

664
00:41:56,887 --> 00:41:59,880
Personally, I understand what's going on there.

665
00:42:00,330 --> 00:42:06,237
Everything is visible in their appearance
when they come out of captivity.

666
00:42:06,529 --> 00:42:10,190
Personally, I'm not interested. I never asked about it.

667
00:42:10,215 --> 00:42:18,507
If a person talks about it, just remembers the topic during
the conversation. 'We had it like that.' I would listen.

668
00:42:18,532 --> 00:42:23,920
I never ask, why, how, tell me. It's unpleasant for me to hear.

669
00:42:24,631 --> 00:42:26,930
I don't even talk about...

670
00:42:26,955 --> 00:42:28,552
How they survived it.

671
00:42:29,949 --> 00:42:38,893
Well, such fighters, such warriors,
can you recognise them among personnel?

672
00:42:38,918 --> 00:42:40,981
Are clearly visible?

673
00:42:41,006 --> 00:42:41,533
Yes.

674
00:42:42,033 --> 00:42:45,043
Certainly, there are no others here.

675
00:42:45,820 --> 00:42:53,694
Of course, I completed the last combat mission.

676
00:42:53,719 --> 00:42:59,920
In general, I have a very young platoon.
All the guys are born starting from 2000.

677
00:43:01,385 --> 00:43:05,895
There are from 2002, 2003, 2004, even 2005.

678
00:43:05,920 --> 00:43:06,773
Wow.

679
00:43:06,798 --> 00:43:19,134
Yes, and I just set a task for a person, and as much as I
am a psychologist, I immediately scan the reception.

680
00:43:19,586 --> 00:43:22,150
I don't see any doubts in their eyes.

681
00:43:22,904 --> 00:43:28,638
Or any pause, or that he is doubting something.

682
00:43:28,663 --> 00:43:32,651
A person completes the task.

683
00:43:32,676 --> 00:43:35,290
How did you earn this trust?

684
00:43:35,325 --> 00:43:46,159
Well, probably with the same system,
that I have never let them down.

685
00:43:48,150 --> 00:43:50,870
Do you have to be completely honest with your subordinates?

686
00:43:50,895 --> 00:43:51,895
Never.

687
00:43:51,920 --> 00:43:52,654
You can't.

688
00:43:52,679 --> 00:43:55,920
Once you slip up, and that's it.
There will be no trust.

689
00:43:55,920 --> 00:43:57,920
You will not have that authority.

690
00:43:57,920 --> 00:43:59,920
You should say directly what awaits them?

691
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:07,645
To say what awaits them as much as it is necessary
for them, as much as they are ready to accept it.

692
00:44:07,670 --> 00:44:10,739
This is such a balance, you know.

693
00:44:10,824 --> 00:44:12,824
This must be understood.

694
00:44:12,849 --> 00:44:17,849
One needs to be given full information, one needs
only a part, and another needs to be given nothing.

695
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:20,991
It's like, you know, being a conductor.

696
00:44:21,571 --> 00:44:24,287
A creative person to command.

697
00:44:24,312 --> 00:44:27,698
Because each person has a personality.

698
00:44:27,920 --> 00:44:32,920
And someone needs a kick, and someone just needs a conversation.

699
00:44:34,491 --> 00:44:42,920
You will know how to approach them only when you
are constantly on the same wavelength with them.

700
00:44:43,595 --> 00:44:47,722
And you will understand who is who.

701
00:44:47,747 --> 00:44:49,725
You need to live the lives of your fighters.

702
00:44:49,750 --> 00:44:59,920
I'll tell you that when I think about how you can ask,
force, demand from a person to leave the Azovstal

703
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:03,446
when the person is in a complete block and surrounded.

704
00:45:04,485 --> 00:45:10,756
The human brain understands that you are going to meet death.

705
00:45:10,781 --> 00:45:13,746
How can you give such an order as a commander?

706
00:45:13,771 --> 00:45:16,920
How can you convince a person to go and do it?

707
00:45:17,405 --> 00:45:18,405
Look, here ...

708
00:45:19,379 --> 00:45:20,929
How did they do it?

709
00:45:20,954 --> 00:45:27,029
They did it, I think, based on their full trust in their commander.

710
00:45:27,054 --> 00:45:27,869
Yes, it is true.

711
00:45:27,894 --> 00:45:31,920
They, in the first place, for their commander, can go to the end

712
00:45:31,920 --> 00:45:36,895
and perform the most difficult task in general.

713
00:45:36,920 --> 00:45:38,920
We trust our commander.

714
00:45:38,920 --> 00:45:41,920
They give us tasks, and we perform them.

715
00:45:41,920 --> 00:45:46,920
This is, perhaps, one of the few links

716
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:53,379
that distinguish us from other units and in general in the world.

717
00:45:53,404 --> 00:45:57,920
Because we completely trust our commander.

718
00:45:57,920 --> 00:45:58,920
Completely.

719
00:45:59,282 --> 00:46:00,920
And all our guys.

720
00:46:01,158 --> 00:46:03,920
The commander has a great deal of authority.

721
00:46:06,681 --> 00:46:11,920
With all these years, when the war is still going on, it is only growing.

722
00:46:15,273 --> 00:46:16,577
I will say one thing.

723
00:46:16,602 --> 00:46:23,920
The commander of the company, the commander of
the battalion, the commander of the brigade.

724
00:46:23,920 --> 00:46:27,920
These are, I think, the most competent people,

725
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:30,442
the most authoritative people for me.

726
00:46:31,920 --> 00:46:33,544
I don't need anything else.

727
00:46:33,569 --> 00:46:35,686
Well, it's worth serving with people like that.

728
00:46:35,711 --> 00:46:36,920
Yes, that's all.

729
00:46:37,369 --> 00:46:38,393
Even, you know ...

730
00:46:38,418 --> 00:46:39,540
Under their leadership.

731
00:46:39,565 --> 00:46:42,565
Our company commander.

732
00:46:42,920 --> 00:46:50,895
We communicate with him long enough, for me it`s clearly to
understand when he is my friend and when he is my leader.

733
00:46:51,648 --> 00:46:54,920
I don't need to be reminded of it many times.

734
00:46:54,945 --> 00:46:56,945
How not to cross the line?

735
00:46:57,903 --> 00:46:59,920
Well, at work, when there is work, we ...

736
00:46:59,920 --> 00:47:01,920
I know when he is my friend,

737
00:47:01,920 --> 00:47:02,920
I know when he is my commander.

738
00:47:02,920 --> 00:47:04,611
We work as commanders and subordinates.

739
00:47:04,636 --> 00:47:11,920
Sometimes we can come to talk to him,
go somewhere, drink coffee, have a snack.

740
00:47:12,287 --> 00:47:13,287
Yes.

741
00:47:13,535 --> 00:47:17,920
I talk to him frankly quite often.

742
00:47:18,753 --> 00:47:25,159
I stay with him, and we already have a
dialogue as two friends.

743
00:47:25,417 --> 00:47:31,401
And I told him frankly that, even though...
by the way, a company commander is a few years younger than me,

744
00:47:32,059 --> 00:47:37,248
